<subSubSection id="C3506550FFBDFFFB8FF6F881FDE1C5DB" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BF536DBFFBDFFFB8FF6F881FDE1C5DB" blockId="3.[136,775,1888,1944]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBDFFFB8FF6F881FED3C53B" bold="true" box="[136,265,1888,1912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a Latin adjective referring to the dark prosoma in the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506550FFBDFFFC8FF6F821FEBFC4AD" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="3" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF536DBFFBDFFFB8FF6F821FC68CA5B" blockId="3.[136,775,1984,2072]" lastBlockId="3.[834,1475,1536,2072]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBDFFFB8FF6F821FECFC59B" bold="true" box="[136,277,1984,2008]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Description.</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus id="54F18879FFBDFFFB8E1FF821FE19C59B" box="[353,451,1984,2008]" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">holotype</typeStatus>
. Total length 1.93. Carapace unmodified, 1.03 long, 0.73 wide, dark reddish brown, with an indistinct grey median spot and radial stripes (
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBDFFFB8DCAF7E1FD23CA5B" box="[692,761,2048,2072]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Clypeus below each anterior lateral eye with a narrow and elongated groove (sub-ocular sulci), as in 
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBDFFFB8A7AF9C1FA9FC47B" box="[1284,1349,1568,1592]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
. Chelicerae 0.38 long, anterior margin with one small and two strong teeth, mastidion absent. Legs yellow. Leg I 2.86 long (0.80 + 0.28 + 0.70 + 0.58 + 0.50), IV 2.66 long (0.70 + 0.25 + 0.63 + 0.63 + 0.45). Chaetotaxy: TiI: 2-1-1-0, II: 2-0-1-0, III: 2-0-0-0, IV: 1-0-0-0. Femora and metatarsi unarmed. Length of spines 1–2 diameters of corresponding leg segment. TmI 0.45. Metatarsi IV without trichobothrium. Palp (
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBDFFFB8AF5F8E1FC56C57B" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[136,180,1430,1452]" captionTargetBox="[142,1475,188,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-7@3.[129,1490,182,1419]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 11–15. Details of male palp structure of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (11, 12) and A. atrata, new species, male holotype (13–15). 11, 13, right palp, retrolateral view; 12, 14, right palp, prolateral view; 15, embolic division, mesal view, not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577377" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577377/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Figs. 13–15</figureCitation>
): Patella with a stout spine. Tibia long, subequal in length to cymbium. Cymbium narrow, conical distally, bearing three macrosetae. Paracymbium simple, small, flat, L-shaped. Tegulum with a conical extention distally. Distal suprategular apophysis short and slender. Median membrane very small, poorly visible. Embolus short and narrow, radix small, oblong-oval. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBDFFFB8BEFF801FB0BC5BB" box="[1169,1233,2016,2040]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="59">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) 0.98 long, 0.60 wide, dark grey.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF356653FFBAFFFC8F0FFB6DFB23C6FC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577379" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4577379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577379/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" startId="4.[113,157,1164,1186]" targetBox="[100,1463,181,1153]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BF536DBFFBAFFFC8F0FFB6DFB23C6FC" blockId="4.[113,1451,1164,1215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">
Figs. 16–20. Epigyne and vulva structure of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D58FFBAFFFC8D60FB6DFD02C6E2" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[542,728,1164,1185]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Asiafroneta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBAFFFC8D60FB6DFD02C6E2" box="[542,728,1164,1185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Asiafroneta pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D57B2FFBAFFFC8D9AFB6CFC80C6E1" box="[740,858,1164,1186]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female paratype from Layang Layang (16, 17) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D58FFBAFFFC8A2EFB6CFA7CC6E1" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[1360,1446,1165,1186]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Asiafroneta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBAFFFC8A2EFB6CFA7CC6E1" box="[1360,1446,1165,1186]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">A. atrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D57B2FFBAFFFC8F0FFB4BFF33C6FC" box="[113,233,1193,1215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female paratype (18–20). 16, 18, epigyne, ventral view; 17, 19, 20, vulva, dorsal view, different aspects.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF536DBFFBAFFFC8F0FFB17FEBFC4AD" blockId="4.[112,754,1270,1774]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">
Female. Total length 2.10. Carapace unmodified (
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBAFFFC8DE3FB17FD38C74D" box="[669,738,1270,1294]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), 1.03 long, 0.72 wide. Clypeus below each anterior lateral eye with a narrow and elongated groove (sub-ocular sulci), as in 
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBAFFFC8FD4FAB7FF22C72D" box="[170,248,1366,1390]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
. Chelicerae 0.40 long, anterior margin with one small and two strong teeth, mastidion absent. Legs yellow. Leg I 2.53 long (0.70 + 0.28 + 0.60 + 0.50 + 0.45), IV 2.45 long (0.70 + 0.25 + 0.60 + 0.45 + 0.45). Length of spines 1–2 diameters of corresponding leg segment. TmI 0.46. Metatarsi IV without trichobothrium. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBAFFFC8D08FA17FD6FC44D" box="[630,693,1526,1550]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) 1.15 long, 0.75 wide, grey to dark grey. Epigyne and vulva (
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBAFFFC8DC7F9F7FF5AC40D" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Figs. 8</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBAFFFC8FEEF9D7FF03C40D" box="[144,217,1590,1614]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="4.[113,157,1164,1186]" captionTargetBox="[100,1463,181,1153]" captionTargetId="figure-400@4.[97,1465,181,1176]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs. 16–20. Epigyne and vulva structure of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, female paratype from Layang Layang (16, 17) and A. atrata, new species, female paratype (18–20). 16, 18, epigyne, ventral view; 17, 19, 20, vulva, dorsal view, different aspects." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577379" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577379/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">18–20</figureCitation>
): Epigyne small, anterior wall (= ventral plate, auct.) with a notch, posterior median plate (= dorsal plate, auct.) with a rudimentary parmula (= scapus, auct.), a pit present. Receptacles sub-spherical, median ducts globularly expanded distally, almost in contact. Body colouration and chaetotaxy as in male.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506550FFBAFFFC8F0FF8F7FD4CCA6D" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF536DBFFBAFFFC8F0FF8F7FD4CCA6D" blockId="4.[113,753,1814,2094]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBAFFFC8F0FF8F7FEB1C56D" bold="true" box="[113,363,1814,1838]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
The species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D58FFBAFFFC8DA7F8F6FF67C50D" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Asiafroneta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBAFFFC8DA7F8F6FF67C50D" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">A. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D57B2FFBAFFFC8FB3F8D6FE88C50D" box="[205,338,1846,1870]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the only congener so far known (see above), but both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D58FFBAFFFC8EF6F8B6FE32C52D" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[392,488,1879,1902]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Asiafroneta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBAFFFC8EF6F8B6FE32C52D" box="[392,488,1879,1902]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">A. atrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D57B2FFBAFFFC8E88F8B6FDA0C52D" box="[502,634,1878,1902]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, can easily be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D58FFBAFFFC8E11F896FE07C5CD" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[367,477,1910,1934]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Asiafroneta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallida" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBAFFFC8E11F896FE07C5CD" box="[367,477,1910,1934]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">A. pallida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D57B2FFBAFFFC8E90F896FDACC5CD" box="[494,630,1910,1934]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, by a dark carapace: dark reddish brown vs. pale greyish brown (
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBAFFFC8DC5F877FF41C58D" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Figs. 6, 7</figureCitation>
cf. 
<figureCitation id="13712A5EFFBAFFFC8FB7F857FEEEC58D" box="[201,308,1974,1998]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[113,157,1618,1640]" captionTargetBox="[115,1457,183,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-12@2.[104,1464,178,1616]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–10. Photographs of Asiafroneta pallida, new species, male holotype (1, 4), female paratype from Layang Layang (2, 3, 5); A. atrata, new species, male holotype (6, 9) and female paratype (7, 8, 10). 1, 2, 6, 7, body, dorsal view; 3, 8, posterior part of body, ventral view; 4, 5, 9, 10, prosoma, frontal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4577375" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4577375/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Figs. 1, 2</figureCitation>
). The male differs by both twice shorter embolus and distal suprategular apophysis. The female genitalia in both species are very similar, but the median ducts in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D58FFBAFFFC8FACF7F6FEEACA6D" authority="Tanasevitch, 2020" authorityName="Tanasevitch" authorityYear="2020" box="[210,304,2071,2094]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Asiafroneta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrata" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBAFFFC8FACF7F6FEEACA6D" box="[210,304,2071,2094]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">A. atrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20D57B2FFBAFFFC8E3EF7F6FE1FCA6D" box="[320,453,2070,2094]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, seem to be larger.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506550FFBAFFFC8C53FB17FB78C76D" pageId="4" pageNumber="60" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF536DBFFBAFFFC8C53FB17FB78C76D" blockId="4.[813,1451,1270,1326]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B93EEAC9FFBAFFFC8C53FB17FC65C74D" bold="true" box="[813,959,1270,1294]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54F18879FFBAFFFC8BC3FB16FB31C74C" box="[1213,1259,1271,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingRegion id="498EF839FFBAFFFC8A14FB17FA71C74D" box="[1386,1451,1270,1294]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Sabah</collectingRegion>
(East 
<collectingCountry id="F35D764BFFBAFFFC8C12FAF7FC15C76D" box="[876,975,1302,1326]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="60">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
) on Borneo Island.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
